File: Western Cape Premier, Alan Winde, says the booze ban must be lifted urgently to avoid a jobs bloodbath. JOHANNESBURG - The Western Cape says it's ready to start selling alcohol again. Premier Alan Winde says the booze ban must be lifted urgently to avoid a jobs bloodbath. Winde says having passed the peak of infections there are enough beds to deal with alcohol-related trauma and COVID-19 patients. READ: Liquor Traders Council want alcohol ban lifted Government banned booze sales saying alcohol-related trauma will overwhelm the healthcare system. Winde says the negative impact of the ban is far worse than its benefits. The industry says the ban has hurt many businesses and it's had to retrench workers. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.